{"hash":"6595fd7e47acd9393e40c4ea65488e3a966d3f4c","data":{"markdownPage":{"id":"4fe3023f9083c2e61647f2b035427b32","title":"Installation","description":"","path":"/docs/installation/","timeToRead":1,"content":"<h1 id=\"installation\"><a href=\"#installation\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"icon icon-link\"></span></a>Installation</h1>\n<p><em><strong>Note:</strong> for now there's only a demo project with fixture data as NumberNine is still in development. This will be improved.</em></p>\n<p>Requirements to install NumberNine:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://getcomposer.org/download/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Composer</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://symfony.com/download\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Symfony executable</a></li>\n<li>make (<a href=\"http://gnuwin32.sourceforge.net/packages/make.htm\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Windows version</a>)</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"windows--linux--wsl-installation\"><a href=\"#windows--linux--wsl-installation\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"icon icon-link\"></span></a>Windows / Linux / WSL installation</h2>\n<h3 id=\"create-the-project\"><a href=\"#create-the-project\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"icon icon-link\"></span></a>Create the project</h3>\n<p>To create a new project with NumberNine, simply run:</p>\n<pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token function\">composer</span> create-project numberninecms/demo:dev-develop my_project</code></pre>\n<h3 id=\"launch-installation\"><a href=\"#launch-installation\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"icon icon-link\"></span></a>Launch installation</h3>\n<p>Go to your new project root and run:</p>\n<pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token function\">make</span> <span class=\"token function\">install</span></code></pre>\n<p>An installation wizard will ask you details of your database and create everything for you.</p>\n<h3 id=\"run-the-server\"><a href=\"#run-the-server\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"icon icon-link\"></span></a>Run the server</h3>\n<p>Now launch the local server and visit your website.</p>\n<pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token function\">make</span> serve</code></pre>\n<p>You're done. Visit <a href=\"https://localhost:8080/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">https://localhost:8080/</a> or the given URL if different.</p>\n<h2 id=\"docker\"><a href=\"#docker\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"icon icon-link\"></span></a>Docker</h2>\n<p>To use Docker with NumberNine you need to install <code>composer</code>, <code>make</code> and <code>yarn</code> on your host (WSL, Ubuntu, MacOS, Windows...) as Docker will only serve your application. Files stay on your host.</p>\n<h3 id=\"create-the-project-1\"><a href=\"#create-the-project-1\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"icon icon-link\"></span></a>Create the project</h3>\n<p>To create a new project with NumberNine, simply run:</p>\n<pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token function\">composer</span> create-project numberninecms/demo:dev-develop my_project</code></pre>\n<h3 id=\"build-containers-and-install\"><a href=\"#build-containers-and-install\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"icon icon-link\"></span></a>Build containers and install</h3>\n<p>Go to your new project root and run:</p>\n<pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token function\">make</span> docker-install</code></pre>\n<p>Done. Now visit <a href=\"http://localhost/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">http://localhost/</a></p>\n<p>If you want another domain or port, run:</p>\n<pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token assign-left variable\">SERVER_NAME</span><span class=\"token operator\">=</span>mydomain.wip <span class=\"token assign-left variable\">NGINX_PORT</span><span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token number\">8080</span> docker-compose up</code></pre>\n<h2 id=\"quick-start\"><a href=\"#quick-start\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"icon icon-link\"></span></a>Quick start</h2>\n<p>Either login by clicking the top right \"Login/Register\" link, or by accessing <code>/admin/</code>.</p>\n<p>Demo admin login: <strong>admin</strong><br/>\nDemo admin password: <strong>password</strong></p>\n","sidebar":"docs","next":"","prev":"/docs/screenshots/","headings":[{"depth":1,"value":"Installation","anchor":"#installation"},{"depth":2,"value":"Windows / Linux / WSL installation","anchor":"#windows--linux--wsl-installation"},{"depth":3,"value":"Create the project","anchor":"#create-the-project"},{"depth":3,"value":"Launch installation","anchor":"#launch-installation"},{"depth":3,"value":"Run the server","anchor":"#run-the-server"},{"depth":2,"value":"Docker","anchor":"#docker"},{"depth":3,"value":"Create the project","anchor":"#create-the-project-1"},{"depth":3,"value":"Build containers and install","anchor":"#build-containers-and-install"},{"depth":2,"value":"Quick start","anchor":"#quick-start"}]},"allMarkdownPage":{"edges":[{"node":{"path":"/docs/screenshots/","title":"Screenshots"}},{"node":{"path":"/docs/installation/","title":"Installation"}},{"node":{"path":"/docs/","title":"Introduction"}}]}},"context":{}}